remediationSample:
1.
SELECT DATE_PART('day', '2006-09-21'::date);


2.
A function DAYS can be created as a workaround in Postgre SQL:
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION DAYS (V1 DATE)
RETURNS integer
LANGUAGE plpgsql
AS
$$
BEGIN
RETURN TO_DATE(V1,'YYYY-MM-DD') - TO_DATE('4712-01-01','YYYYMM-DD');
END;
$$;

sample:
1.
SELECT DAY (DATE('2006-09-21'))
FROM SYSIBM.SYSDUMMY1;


2. 
SELECT (DAYS (DATE('2006-09-25')) - DAYS(DATE('2006-09-21')))
FROM SYSIBM.SYSDUMMY1;
